insert into quotes values (395,'Age is not all decay it is the ripening, the swelling, of the fresh life within, that withers and bursts the husk.','George MacDonald');
insert into quotes values (396,'I knew at a young age, whether I was playing baseball or hockey or lacrosse, that my teammates were counting on me, whether it be to strike the last batter out in a baseball game or score a big goal in a hockey game.','Wayne Gretzky');
insert into quotes values (397,'The funniest racism is the racism between minorities. It’s something you don’t see dramatized, but almost every minority I know who’s my age, they have these funny stories about their parents stereotyping other minorities.','Mindy Kaling');
insert into quotes values (398,'It’s ironic that at age 32, at probably the greatest moment of my career, with The Godfather having such an enormous success, I wasn’t even aware of it, because I was somewhere else under the deadline again.','Francis Ford Coppola');
insert into quotes values (399,'I’m asked all the time in interviews about who I am, and I know a few people my age who have a strong sense of self, but I couldn’t say I know myself and sum it up and give it to you in a little package. I don’t know myself at all yet.','Kristen Stewart');
insert into quotes values (400,'Alexander at the head of the world never tasted the true pleasure that boys of his own age have enjoyed at the head of a school.','Horace Walpole');
insert into quotes values (401,'To separate children from others of similar age and qualifications solely because of their race generates a feeling of inferiority as to their status in the community that may affect their hearts and minds in a way unlikely ever to be undone.','Earl Warren');
insert into quotes values (402,'In an age of incompetence, I’ve been able to last in this crazy business. I actually know how to play my ax and write a song. That’s my job.','Billy Joel');
insert into quotes values (403,'In this age of media and Internet access, we are much more talkative than ever before.','David Duchovny');
insert into quotes values (404,'Over the years Woodstock got glorified and romanticised and became the event that symbolised Utopia. It’s the last page of our collective memory of the age of innocence. Then things turned ugly and would never be the same again.','Ang Lee');
insert into quotes values (405,'Every time I see something terrible, it’s like I see it at age 19. I keep a freshness that way.','Ralph Nader');
insert into quotes values (406,'I hate to mention age, but I come from an era when we weren’t consumed by technology and television.','Jimmy Buffett');
insert into quotes values (407,'We are approaching a new age of synthesis. Knowledge cannot be merely a degree or a skill… it demands a broader vision, capabilities in critical thinking and logical deduction without which we cannot have constructive progress.','Li Ka Shing');
insert into quotes values (408,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene');
insert into quotes values (409,'Every age yearns for a more beautiful world. The deeper the desperation and the depression about the confusing present, the more intense that yearning.','Johan Huizinga');
insert into quotes values (410,'To be told that one can be dependent on one’s parents until age 26 should strike a young person who wants to grow up as demeaning, not as something to celebrate.','Dennis Prager');
insert into quotes values (411,'Does age matter? Time doesn’t matter.','Sandra Bullock');
insert into quotes values (412,'I figured out it was a social thing, what women were allowed to do. At a very young age, I decided I was not going to follow women’s rules.','Joan Jett');
insert into quotes values (413,'We were really grown up for our age and it was an incredible special band.','Joan Jett');
insert into quotes values (414,'Age is the first limitation on roles that I’ve ever had to encounter, and I hit that awhile ago.','Jack Nicholson');
insert into quotes values (415,'I can’t hit on women in public any more. I didn’t decide this it just doesn’t feel right at my age.','Jack Nicholson');
insert into quotes values (416,'This is the first age that’s ever paid much attention to the future, which is a little ironic since we may not have one.','Arthur C. Clarke');
insert into quotes values (417,'I feel we live in the kind of culture now where you have to be very smart to navigate the right way, and I just don’t have those smarts. I think with age and time it will change, but I can’t obsess about it.','Sienna Miller');
insert into quotes values (418,'The secret of long life is double careers. One to about age sixty, then another for the next thirty years.','David Ogilvy');
insert into quotes values (419,'I knew at an early age I wanted to act. Acting was always easy for me. I don’t believe in predestination, but I do believe that once you get where ever it is you are going, that is where you were going to be.','Morgan Freeman');
insert into quotes values (420,'The age in which we live, this non-stop distraction, is making it more impossible for the young generation to ever have the curiosity or discipline… because you need to be alone to find out anything.','Vivienne Westwood');
insert into quotes values (421,'I can feel the 60S looming. In my profession, I’ve just moved along with my age. By thinking in decades, rather than whether someone’s 42 or 47, you can give yourself a whole 10 years to turn yourself around in.','Francesca Annis');
insert into quotes values (422,'We all know now that people can look good for their age. It isn’t so extraordinary, I don’t know why people go on about it so much.','Francesca Annis');
insert into quotes values (423,'A lot of music you might listen to is pretty vapid, it doesn’t always deal with our deeper issues. These are the things I’m interested in now, particularly at my age.','Annie Lennox');
insert into quotes values (424,'Life expectancy in many parts of Africa can be something around the age of thirty five to thirty eight. I mean you’re very fortunate if you live to that age. In fact when I went to Uganda for the first time one of the things that occurred to me was that I saw very few elderly people.','Annie Lennox');
insert into quotes values (425,'Light and funny has a more compelling quality when you’re younger. But I haven’t abandoned the genre: I love falling down I love Lucille Ball. It’s just that a lot of those stories revolve around problems that I can’t convincingly portray at this age.','Julia Roberts');
insert into quotes values (426,'I had the good fortune to be able to right an injustice that I thought was being heaped on young people by lowering the voting age, where you had young people that were old enough to die in Vietnam but not old enough to vote for their members of Congress that sent them there.','Birch Bayh');
insert into quotes values (427,'The value of old age depends upon the person who reaches it. To some men of early performance it is useless. To others, who are late to develop, it just enables them to finish the job.','Thomas Hardy');
insert into quotes values (428,'I’ve gotten crankier in my old age.','Shirley MacLaine');
insert into quotes values (429,'I’ve been very competitive by nature from a young age, whether it was eating a bowl of pasta faster than somebody else, or always wanting to be the first one in line.','Maria Sharapova');
insert into quotes values (430,'Death comes not to the living soul, nor age to the loving heart.','Phoebe Cary');
insert into quotes values (431,'I’m not busy… a woman with three children under the age of 10 wouldn’t think my schedule looked so busy.','Garrison Keillor');
insert into quotes values (432,'High expectations weren’t nurtured in my neck of nowhere back then','children weren’t fawned over from an early age as ‘gifted’ and groomed for a prizewinning future self-esteem was considered something you had to pick from the garden yourself.');
insert into quotes values (433,'Not by age but by capacity is wisdom acquired.','Plautus');
insert into quotes values (434,'Whoever marries the spirit of this age will find himself a widower in the next.','William Ralph Inge');
insert into quotes values (435,'Of middle age the best that can be said is that a middle-aged person has likely learned how to have a little fun in spite of his troubles.','Don Marquis');
insert into quotes values (436,'Old age is always wakeful as if, the longer linked with life, the less man has to do with aught that looks like death.','Herman Melville');
insert into quotes values (437,'What I think is amazing is not that 85% of people who get married under the age of 25 get divorced, it’s that 15% of them stay together. How did they manage to pull that off? You almost can’t wait too long. It’s the single simplest measure to predict divorce.','Elizabeth Gilbert');
insert into quotes values (438,'I avoid talking before the youth of the age as I would dancing before them: for if one’s tongue don’t move in the steps of the day, and thinks to please by its old graces, it is only an object of ridicule.','Horace Walpole');
insert into quotes values (439,'I’m glad I was born when I was. My time was the golden age of variety. If I were starting out again now, maybe things would happen for me, but it certainly would not be on a variety show with 28 musicians, 12 dancers, two major guest stars, 50 costumes a week by Bob Mackie. The networks just wouldn’t spend the money today.','Carol Burnett');
insert into quotes values (440,'I was taught from a young age that many people would treat me as a second-class citizen because I was African-American and because I was female.','Queen Latifah');
insert into quotes values (441,'Even from a very early age, I knew I didn’t want to miss out on anything life had to offer just because it might be considered dangerous.','Nicole Kidman');
insert into quotes values (442,'We live in an age where anonymity is growing in magnitude like a bomb going off.','Jock Sturges');
insert into quotes values (443,'I was a mixture of being incredibly old for my age and incredibly backwards. I was born quite old, but then I stopped growing. I lived with my mum and dad till I was 30.','Helena Bonham Carter');
insert into quotes values (444,'The Word of fire burns today On the lips of our prophets in an evil age.','Margaret Walker');
insert into quotes values (445,'What is wrong with the Iranians in addition to the nuclear bomb? This is the only country on Earth in the 21st century that has renewed imperialistic ambitions. They really want to become the hegemon of the Middle East in an age that gave up imperialism.','Shimon Peres');
insert into quotes values (446,'I think it’s quite extraordinary that people cast me as if I’m Warren Beatty: until I met my present wife, at the age of 35, you could name two girlfriends.','Colin Firth');
insert into quotes values (447,'Craziest thing I’ve done for love is getting married. I think it’s crazy. I think it’s crazy, crazy, crazy. I’m never going to say I wouldn’t do it again but I have to make sure it’s love and not settling for the ‘I have to do this by a certain age,’ which is kind of what I did.','Jenny McCarthy');
insert into quotes values (448,'You never choose the way that you’re raised, it’s just the way that you were raised, but you do get to a certain age where you’re in a position to question the expectations of you and the way that you’ve been formed by your surroundings.','Mia Wasikowska');
insert into quotes values (449,'We tried not to age, but time had its rage.','Pete Townshend');
insert into quotes values (450,'I want to age with some dignity.','Pete Townshend');
insert into quotes values (451,'This is my 20th year in the sport. I’ve known swimming and that’s it. I don’t want to swim past age 30 if I continue after this Olympics, and come back in 2016, I’ll be 31. I’m looking forward to being able to see the other side of the fence.','Michael Phelps');
insert into quotes values (452,'Young man, the secret of my success is that an early age I discovered that I was not God.','Oliver Wendell Holmes, Jr.');
insert into quotes values (453,'I’d like to talk about free markets. Information in the computer age is the last genuine free market left on earth except those free markets where indigenous people are still surviving. And that’s basically becoming limited.','Russell Means');
insert into quotes values (454,'I would often find myself, at the age of 21, at midnight, running down a dark street on my own with 10 men chasing me. And the fact they had cameras in their hands made that legal.','Sienna Miller');
insert into quotes values (455,'Bring a wife home to your house when you are of the right age, not far short of 30 years, nor much above this is the right time for marriage.','Hesiod');
insert into quotes values (456,'There are only two things a child will share willingly communicable diseases and its mother’s age.','Benjamin Spock');
insert into quotes values (457,'Although it is generally known, I think it’s about time to announce that I was born at a very early age.','Douglas Horton');
insert into quotes values (458,'I think it’s your mental attitude. So many of us start dreading age in high school and that’s a waste of a lovely life. ‘Oh… I’m 30, oh, I’m 40, oh, 50.’ Make the most of it.','Betty White');
insert into quotes values (459,'No, no, I was only funny on stage, really. I, I, think I was funny as a person toward my classmates when I was very young. You know, when I was a child, up to about the age of 12.','Rowan Atkinson');
insert into quotes values (460,'What goes on in Europe concerns us greatly because, if Europe comes apart, the E.U. comes apart, then you’re going to have enormous impact on America, that’s a very big trading partner of ours, and people own securities around the world in this day and age.','Michael Bloomberg');
insert into quotes values (461,'Your body actually reminds you about your age and your injuries','the body has a stronger memory than your mind.');
insert into quotes values (462,'People dance at any age.','Mikhail Baryshnikov');
insert into quotes values (463,'I never had little brothers, so I was totally not used to hearing a lot of cussing at a young age! I learned what ‘pull my finger’ meant the hard way.','Danica McKellar');
insert into quotes values (464,'My sister and I shared a bedroom our entire lives and I believe she discovered the Beatles when she was about 11 and I’m four years younger. So from the age of 7 until 17 we had nothing but Beatles paraphernalia in our room, even those little stuffed Beatles that went on stands that are dressed as the Sgt. Pepper band.','Christina Ricci');
insert into quotes values (465,'But look, I was born in 1956, the peak year for births in US history. I think I’m very representative of many of the thought processes my generation have been through and, by and large, people of my age have had their imprint planted on the consciousness of western society for a long time.','Tom Hanks');
insert into quotes values (466,'I basically get stereotyped a lot in terms of being a girl and writing ‘chick’ music for teenage girls or something. I think, if anything, the press kind of, because of my gender and my age, tends to kind of relegate my work to this sort of special-interest group. It’s part of the cultural dynamic, I guess.','Ani DiFranco');
insert into quotes values (467,'What is amazing for a woman of my age is that I change as the world is changing-and changing very, very fast. I don’t think my mother had that opportunity to change.','Jeanne Moreau');
insert into quotes values (468,'I’ve never worried about age.','Jeanne Moreau');
insert into quotes values (469,'To me age is a number, just a number. Who cares?','Jeanne Moreau');
insert into quotes values (470,'If you’re extremely, painfully frightened of age, it shows.','Jeanne Moreau');
insert into quotes values (471,'For a man who has compared himself to Theodore Roosevelt and the nation’s challenges to those of the Gilded Age, Obama put forward a tepid agenda.','Ron Fournier');
insert into quotes values (472,'I wrote a screenplay for a ‘Sweet Valley High’ adaptation, and it’s really amazing to me how many women who are my age have responded to the idea and are excited about the movie.','Diablo Cody');
insert into quotes values (473,'Let age, not envy, draw wrinkles on thy cheeks.','Thomas Browne');
insert into quotes values (474,'Here’s my Golden Rule for a tarnished age: Be fair with others, but keep after them until they’re fair with you.','Alan Alda');
insert into quotes values (475,'Children under five are the poorest age group in America, and one in four infants, toddlers and preschoolers are poor during the years of greatest brain development.','Marian Wright Edelman');
insert into quotes values (476,'Everyone talks about age, but it’s not about age. It’s about work ethic. Winning never gets old.','Lisa Leslie');
insert into quotes values (477,'Age is a terrible avenger. The lessons of life give you so much to work with, but by the time you’ve got all this great wisdom, you don’t get to be young anymore.','Elizabeth Wurtzel');
insert into quotes values (478,'Science cannot tell theology how to construct a doctrine of creation, but you can’t construct a doctrine of creation without taking account of the age of the universe and the evolutionary character of cosmic history.','John Polkinghorne');
insert into quotes values (479,'I came of age believing that, no matter what happened, I would always be able to support myself.','William J. Clinton');
insert into quotes values (480,'Dallas’ hit a chord back in the late Seventies and Eighties because it was the age of greed: here you have this unapologetic character who is mean and nasty and ruthless and does it all with an evil grin. I think people related to JR back then because we all have someone we know exactly like him. Everyone in the world knows a JR.- Larry Hagman','');
insert into quotes values (481,'It is not classified as a pagan religion. The so-called New Age activities and this are not called religions and therefore don’t come under the prohibition of mingling church and state that we have in this country.','Dixie Lee Ray');
insert into quotes values (482,'No sex, age, or condition is above or below the absolute necessity of modesty but without it one vastly beneath the rank of man.','Bruce Barton');
insert into quotes values (483,'People tend to become more emotionally intelligent as they age and mature.','Daniel Goleman');
insert into quotes values (484,'With age, you get to a place where you don’t want to knock people out. You just want to give people a hug.','Vin Diesel');
insert into quotes values (485,'Age is no barrier. It’s a limitation you put on your mind.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee');
insert into quotes values (486,'Whoever, fleeing marriage and the sorrows that women cause, does not wish to wed comes to a deadly old age.','Hesiod');
insert into quotes values (487,'Age has been the perfect fire extinguisher for flaming youth.','Navjot Singh Sidhu');
insert into quotes values (488,'I prefer younger men. In some ways, they are much more open to a woman being stronger and independent then some of the men my age.','Kim Cattrall');
insert into quotes values (489,'You have to be desirable. And that’s why so many woman of my age or even younger are pushed to Botox and plastic surgery, all the things that people say, ‘Why do women do this?’ Where do you go in your 50s in your career?','Kim Cattrall');
insert into quotes values (490,'It is my art. I am better at it than I ever was. And I will do it as long as I can. When you reach a certain age you can slough off what is unnecessary and concentrate on what is. And why not?','Arthur Miller');
insert into quotes values (491,'I feel like a lot of the female relationships I see on TV or in movies are in some way free of the kind of jealousy and anxiety and posturing that has been such a huge part of my female friendships, which I hope lessens a little bit with age.','Lena Dunham');
insert into quotes values (492,'At my age, no one is married, no one has kids, no one has a career.','Lena Dunham');
insert into quotes values (493,'One of the many pleasures of old age is giving things up.','Malcolm Muggeridge');
insert into quotes values (494,'There’s also some element of coming of age during the Reagan administration, which everybody has painted as some glorious time in America, but I remember as being a very, very dark time. There was apocalypse in the air the punk rock movement made sense.','John Cusack');
insert into quotes values (495,'If you explode onto the scene at a very young age, there are so many people pulling you in different directions. It takes time to recalibrate and see what’s important.','Clive Owen');
insert into quotes values (496,'Situational unawareness in the private marketplace or on the battlefield will cost you your livelihood or your life. In the Age of Obama, however, such willful ignorance is a job prerequisite. The less you know the better.','Michelle Malkin');
insert into quotes values (497,'We virtually never feel our age, but thinking that we should can lead to disaster.','Martha Beck');
insert into quotes values (498,'We grew up in a very creative environment and were exposed to the arts at a very young age, so it’s not a surprise that all of us are in some form of the arts.','Spike Lee');
insert into quotes values (499,'I want to be part of the resurgence of things that are tangible, beautiful and soulful, rather than just give in to the digital age. But when I talk to people about this they just say, ‘Yeah, I know what you mean,’ and stare at their mobiles.','Jack White');
insert into quotes values (500,'I wanted to do two things when I was growing up, about your age. I wanted to play in the NBA, and I wanted to be a businessman after my basketball career was over, and that is what I am doing now.','Magic Johnson');
insert into quotes values (501,'The idea of regretting not doing this seemed insane to me. Sitting in the corner at a bar at age 60, saying: ‘I could’ve been Bond. Buy me a drink.’ That’s the saddest place I could be. At least now at 60 I can say: ‘I was Bond. Now buy me a drink.’','Daniel Craig');
insert into quotes values (502,'There’s a vintage which comes with age and experience.','Jon Bon Jovi');
insert into quotes values (503,'It’s not the normal way to look at things but I experienced death at a really young age and because of that it’s been part of my mental landscape that death is really very possible.','Cate Blanchett');
insert into quotes values (504,'I’ve an enormous respect for my mother who at the age of 39 raised three children, and I grew up with my grandmother in the household. And so it was a really strong household of women','my poor brother! It was great growing up with so many generations of women.');
insert into quotes values (505,'Every age develops its own peculiar forms of pathology, which express in exaggerated form its underlying character structure.','Christopher Lasch');
insert into quotes values (506,'I love my kids, and the moments I have with them, and it’s kind of weird, it’s such an age old cliche, but the way that my sons, the way they make me feel when I look at them, the way they say things, no one else would probably react to them, but it’s a special thing for me.','Michael Rapaport');
insert into quotes values (507,'There’s a very small group of elite actresses who are my age, who people want to work with. It’s not easy to get a good job with good actors.','Amanda Peet');
insert into quotes values (508,'A final word: I am not knowledgeable about the internet. I do not have a computer. I guess that at 74 years of age, I don’t have the patience to learn.','David Wilkerson');
insert into quotes values (509,'It lies in human nature that where you experience your first laughs, you also remember the age kindly.','Vaclav Havel');
insert into quotes values (510,'We tried not to age, but time had its rage.','Patti Smith');
insert into quotes values (511,'Michelle Pfeiffer hasn’t been finding a lot of work recently because she doesn’t like what a woman her age is offered. That’s a real double standard. You get Sean Connery, who gets older and older, still playing opposite young ladies, but it doesn’t work the other way around.','Denzel Washington');
insert into quotes values (512,'Old age and treachery will always beat youth and exuberance.','David Mamet');
insert into quotes values (513,'My wife and I, unlike many intellectuals, spent five years working on assembly lines. We came to fully understand the criticisms of the industrial age, in which you are an appendage of a machine that sets the pace.','Alvin Toffler');
insert into quotes values (514,'Even one voice can be heard loudly all over the world in this day and age.','Aung San Suu Kyi');
insert into quotes values (515,'At this age, I should be leading a quiet life.','Aung San Suu Kyi');
insert into quotes values (516,'Any new financial order for the world must tackle the three chief challenges of our age.','James Buchan');
insert into quotes values (517,'There are signs that the age of petroleum has passed its zenith. Adjusted for inflation, a barrel of crude oil now sells for three times its long-run average. The large western oil companies, which cartellised the industry for much of the 20th century, are now selling more oil than they find, and are thus in the throes of liquidation.','James Buchan');
insert into quotes values (518,'With the song ‘This Christmas’ I wanted to do something that was kind of different. I mean, Donny Hathaway is an amazing artist. So I wanted to bring my flavor to the song so when people over the age of 45 or 50 hear it they’ll be like ‘OK, he did his thing with that record.’ It’s like I can appeal to everybody and not just a younger demographic.','Chris Brown');
insert into quotes values (519,'In an age when the fashion is to be in love with yourself, confessing to be in love with somebody else is an admission of unfaithfulness to one’s beloved.','Russell Baker');
insert into quotes values (520,'Rereading A.J. Liebling carries me happily back to an age when all good journalists knew they had plenty to be modest about, and were.','Russell Baker');
insert into quotes values (521,'Reason is a crutch for age, but youth is strong enough to walk alone.','John Dryden');
insert into quotes values (522,'What’s a man’s age? He must hurry more, that’s all Cram in a day, what his youth took a year to hold.','Robert Browning');
insert into quotes values (523,'What Youth deemed crystal, Age finds out was dew.','Robert Browning');
insert into quotes values (524,'may also like  Best 100 Good Morning Quotes and Messages To Start Your day','');
insert into quotes values (525,'A face to lose youth for, to occupy age With the dream of, meet death with.','Robert Browning');
insert into quotes values (526,'I believe the true function of age is memory. I’m recording as fast as I can.','Rita Mae Brown');
insert into quotes values (527,'So Harry Potter came in and it is nice that I have kids of the right age. I took them to London and they walked around the set and met Harry Potter and that is thrilling.','Gary Oldman');
insert into quotes values (528,'All we can do when we think of kids today is think of more hours of school, earlier age at the computer, and curfews. Who would want to grow up in that world?','James Hillman');
insert into quotes values (529,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt');
insert into quotes values (530,'No, but way before that, I’ve been doing little dances in movies for years. Yeah, that was an amazing chance. You know, at my age to be able to do a music dance video, very unusual.','Christopher Walken');
insert into quotes values (531,'There probably aren’t a lot of actors my age who tap dance.','Christopher Walken');
insert into quotes values (532,'I started auditioning when I was about 10 and I didn’t get my first job until I was 12, and two years at that age is really hard.','Anna Kendrick');
insert into quotes values (533,'I remember being in Hollywood at the age of 16 and marveling at the stars. The idea of being part of it never entered my mind. It was too far-fetched.','Bryan Adams');
insert into quotes values (534,'The older generation had greater respect for land than science. But we live in an age when science, more than soil, has become the provider of growth and abundance. Living just on the land creates loneliness in an age of globality.','Shimon Peres');
insert into quotes values (535,'One of my grandfathers, actually, having gone out there as a minister, decided he would better serve the people as a doctor. So at a very late age','at the age of 38 in fact');
insert into quotes values (536,'I’m totally into new age and self-help books. I used to work in a bookstore and that’s the section they gave me, and I got way into it. I just loved the power of positive thinking, letting yourself go.','Jason Mraz');
insert into quotes values (537,'It’s the kind of clothes that mothers and daughters can wear, in terms of concept… It’s not about age. It’s about taste, and it’s about lifestyle. I believe women of all ages can wear anything.','Ralph Lauren');
insert into quotes values (538,'The reason for the slow progress of the world seems to lie in a single fact. Every man is born under the yoke, and grows up beneath the oppressions of his age.','John Jay Chapman');
insert into quotes values (539,'A newspaper is lumber made malleable. It is ink made into words and pictures. It is conceived, born, grows up and dies of old age in a day.','Jim Bishop');
insert into quotes values (540,'Just as we reject racism, sexism, ageism, and heterosexism, we reject speciesism. The species of a sentient being is no more reason to deny the protection of this basic right than race, sex, age, or sexual orientation is a reason to deny membership in the human moral community to other humans.','Gary L. Francione');
insert into quotes values (541,'I am a grandmother now, and that means age is creeping on, creeping on.','Lillie Langtry');
insert into quotes values (542,'I love things that age well','things that don’t date, that stand the test of time and that become living examples of the absolute best.');
insert into quotes values (543,'Many women my age have known the experience of giving up crucial parts of themselves to please the man they love.','Joyce Maynard');
insert into quotes values (544,'American Idol transcends age, gender, ethnicity, everything.','Carrie Underwood');
insert into quotes values (545,'You get to a certain age and you can’t judge yourself on your dad or your parents.','Ellie Goulding');
insert into quotes values (546,'I’d like to look like Madonna when I’m her age. I also look at athletes and love their bodies. I’ve always wanted to be muscly, not skinny. A lot of women yo-yo around, but I’m always aware if I’m getting a bit out of shape. I never look at the scales but I can just tell. It goes on my tum and bum.','Ellie Goulding');
insert into quotes values (547,'I could always sing, from a really young age, but my voice was really weird. I used to make my mum turn up the radio every day in our house. She was well into music so I got that from her.','Ellie Goulding');
insert into quotes values (548,'I think women get caught up too much in having a plan','‘I’m going to get married at this age I’m going to have a kid at this age’');
insert into quotes values (549,'I was always concerned with writing to my age at a particular moment. That was the way I would keep faith with the audience that supported me as I went along.','Bruce Springsteen');
insert into quotes values (550,'Experts tell us that 90% of all brain development occurs by the age of five. If we don’t begin thinking about education in the early years, our children are at risk of falling behind by the time they start Kindergarten.','Robert. L. Ehrlich');
insert into quotes values (551,'When I was seventeen, I worked as a counsellor at a co-ed sleep-away camp for eight weeks. I loved it but it could be harrowing','it was far too much responsibility for someone my age.');
insert into quotes values (552,'Music has always been my protection against the world, from a very young age. I feel safe inside of a jam.','Trey Anastasio');
insert into quotes values (553,'We are the children of a technological age. We have found streamlined ways of doing much of our routine work. Printing is no longer the only way of reproducing books. Reading them, however, has not changed.','Lawrence Clark Powell');
insert into quotes values (554,'Religion is the best antidote to the individualism of the consumer age. The idea that society can do without it flies in the face of history and, now, evolutionary biology.','Jonathan Sacks');
insert into quotes values (555,'Religiosity turns out to be the best indicator of civic involvement: it’s more accurate than education, age, income, gender or race.','Jonathan Sacks');
insert into quotes values (556,'The year I was born, 1956, was the peak year for babies being born, and there are more people essentially our age than anybody else. We could crush these new generations if we decided too.','Tom Hanks');
insert into quotes values (557,'Adulthood is the ever-shrinking period between childhood and old age. It is the apparent aim of modern industrial societies to reduce this period to a minimum.','Thomas Szasz');
insert into quotes values (558,'I was born at the age of twelve on a Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer lot.','Edward Koch');
insert into quotes values (559,'We live in an age of instant knowledge. And there’s almost a sense of entitlement to that.','J. J. Abrams');
insert into quotes values (560,'It’s the golden age of French cinema again but it’s because Sarkozy had the guts to push through copyright law.','Harvey Weinstein');
insert into quotes values (561,'I started in the restaurant business at the age of 19 as a waitress. I loved the atmosphere and the camaraderie of the restaurant business. I loved not having to go to an office. I loved making people happy.','Anne Burrell');
insert into quotes values (562,'My view is pensioners don’t have the one option that people of working age have. They can’t really increase their income, because they are no longer able to work.','Iain Duncan Smith');
insert into quotes values (563,'Work is transformative. It gives you a greater chance of a greater income. You can affect your life while you’re of working age, so you have scope and opportunity. Pensioners do not.','Iain Duncan Smith');
insert into quotes values (564,'I think you can’t really escape any kind of spiritual education as a child, whether it’s New Age or Judaism or Buddhism or whatever it is. You can’t escape it, even if you completely disagree with it, you still have it as a foundation that you base things off of.','Jack White');
insert into quotes values (565,'At my age the only problem is with remembering names. When I call everyone darling, it has damn all to do with passionately adoring them, but I know I’m safe calling them that. Although, of course, I adore them too.','Richard Attenborough');
insert into quotes values (566,'What I really tried to do with Helen was make her show this sad side of her. She was married off at 16, was so young and living in this castle that can’t leave because of how she looks, and married to a man she hates and three times her age.','Diane Kruger');
insert into quotes values (567,'I never took guitar lessons. I took classical piano lessons from the age of six when we lived in Holland. And when we moved to America, it was just the typical thing except I was really good at it so was my brother.','Eddie Van Halen');
insert into quotes values (568,'I never took guitar lessons. I took classical piano lessons from the age of six when we lived in Holland.','Eddie Van Halen');
insert into quotes values (569,'When I write about a 15-year old, I jump, I return to the days when I was that age. It’s like a time machine. I can remember everything. I can feel the wind. I can smell the air. Very actually. Very vividly.','Haruki Murakami');
insert into quotes values (570,'We live in an age, in an era where there is so much negativity, there is so much violence in the world, there is so much unrest and people are at war, that I wanted to promote the word love and red signifies love.','Elton John');
insert into quotes values (571,'I’m 20 years old. I like to party as much as anyone my age. Going clubbing is my way of relaxing or releasing a lot of stress. I don’t feel that I should have to justify that part of my life. I don’t know that I’m necessarily an addict.','Lindsay Lohan');
insert into quotes values (572,'I am happy being able to play roles with people my age because once you do something really mature there is no turning back.','Lindsay Lohan');
insert into quotes values (573,'Compared to a lot of actresses my age, I’m actually overweight.','Lindsay Lohan');
insert into quotes values (574,'This is what I asked for, and in this day and age that’s what actually goes on. But what hurts me the most is that I work just as hard as any other actress around my age, like Scarlett Johansson, but I just don’t get the opportunities that they get because people are so distracted by the mess that I created in my life.','Lindsay Lohan');
insert into quotes values (575,'At a young age, I was interested in comic books, which was really how I learnt to read. The name Cage came from a comic book character called Power Man.','Nicolas Cage');
insert into quotes values (576,'There is a certain age at which a child looks at you in all earnestness and delivers a long, pleased speech in all the true inflections of spoken English, but with not one recognizable syllable.','Annie Dillard');
insert into quotes values (577,'I can’t wait to be that age and hanging out with a bunch of people hanging out all day playing golf and going to the beach, all my own age. We’d be laughing and having a good time and getting loopy on our prescription drugs. Driving golf carts around. I can’t wait.','Cameron Diaz');
insert into quotes values (578,'I would love a family. I’m at the age where the wish for a child gets stronger. But who knows.','Cameron Diaz');
insert into quotes values (579,'I love physical kinds of comedy and getting down and dirty and doing stunts. When I was growing up, I was always getting into fights with guys and usually punching out boys my age because I was a lot bigger and tougher. So I’m naturally accustomed to putting myself into the headspace of a girl who can take care of herself.','Cameron Diaz');
insert into quotes values (580,'Love, with very young people, is a heartless business. We drink at that age from thirst, or to get drunk it is only later in life that we occupy ourselves with the individuality of our wine.','Isak Dinesen');
insert into quotes values (581,'Age for me is just a number.','Haile Gebrselassie');
insert into quotes values (582,'You hit a certain age and','especially because of TV');
insert into quotes values (583,'Some of your teachers are actually closer in age to you than you think.','Maya Lin');
insert into quotes values (584,'From an early age I didn’t buy into the value systems of working hard in a nine-to-five job. I thought creativity, friendship and loyalty and pushing the boundaries of what was acceptable was much more interesting.','Adam Clayton');
insert into quotes values (585,'I didn’t have any success in show business until I was 30 to 31 years of age.','Adam Carolla');
insert into quotes values (586,'I hate the idea that you shouldn’t wear something just because you’re a certain age.','Miuccia Prada');
insert into quotes values (587,'I am firmly of the opinion that women who make a lot of effort to hang onto their looks in middle age (unless they are beauties, entertainers or prostitutes) are rather sad, as one should surely have something more substantial to recommend one by this time, such as kindness or cleverness.','Julie Burchill');
insert into quotes values (588,'As a precocious teen I dreamed of being Graham Greene. Well, as it turned out, I never wrote a great novel, sadly, and I never converted to Catholicism, happily, but I did do one thing he did. That is, in middle age I moved to a seaside town and got into a right barney with the local powers-that-be.','Julie Burchill');
insert into quotes values (589,'Age should not have its face lifted, but it should rather teach the world to admire wrinkles as the etchings of experience and the firm line of character.','Clarence Day');
insert into quotes values (590,'Age is only a number, a cipher for the records. A man can’t retire his experience. He must use it. Experience achieves more with less energy and time.','Bernard Baruch');
insert into quotes values (591,'To me, old age is always fifteen years older than I am.','Bernard Baruch');
insert into quotes values (592,'I wear clothes that most people in the Midwest would probably deem inappropriate at my age. And I rock a bikini all summer long. I know that it’s not normal, but I just don’t care. I live once.','Liz Phair');
insert into quotes values (593,'I’ve lost touch with a lot of that boutique-type music just because of my age, and raising my son and the multiple jobs I have at this point.','Liz Phair');
insert into quotes values (594,'There’s no way to approach anything in an objective way. We’re completely subjective our view of the world is completely controlled by who we are as human beings, as men or women, by our age, our history, our profession, by the state of the world.','Charlie Kaufman');
insert into quotes values (595,'Age is not measured by years. Nature does not equally distribute energy. Some people are born old and tired while others are going strong at seventy.','Dorothy Thompson');
insert into quotes values (596,'Maybe it is something to do with age, but I have become fonder of poetry than of prose.','Aung San Suu Kyi');
insert into quotes values (597,'When I was younger, my whole sense of self-worth was based on whether or not I was working, which was awful. And I had a baby at 20 years old, so it wasn’t just about me. At around the age of 30 there was a stretch where I wasn’t working','certainly not on anything I liked, anyway');
insert into quotes values (598,'I grew up on the golden age of children’s TV.','Edward Norton');
insert into quotes values (599,'I do wish I could tell you my age but it’s impossible. It keeps changing all the time.','Greer Garson');
insert into quotes values (600,'Pretend to be dumb, that’s the only way to reach old age.','Friedrich Durrenmatt');
insert into quotes values (601,'The excitement of learning separates youth from old age. As long as you’re learning you’re not old.','Rosalyn S. Yalow');
insert into quotes values (602,'The history of my life must begin by the earliest circumstance which my memory can evoke it will therefore commence when I had attained the age of eight years and four months.','Giacomo Casanova');
insert into quotes values (603,'We are in an electronic technology age now and it’s about time we put away the old stuff.','Monica Edwards');
insert into quotes values (604,'At the age of 20 I bought a used Fiat 127. This was the only one I could afford!','Carlos Ghosn');
insert into quotes values (605,'At my age, I don’t think anyone is untouched by cancer.','Bryan Cranston');
insert into quotes values (606,'We try, we fail, we posture, we aspire, we pontificate','and then we age, shrink, die, and vanish.');
insert into quotes values (607,'My habit would have been to veer towards the dark','to prove I was something edgy, or maybe to prove that I was cognisant of the dark side. Now, with age and confidence, I can say, yeah, that’s true, but I am cognisant of the fact that people can do things well. And can be more loving than you expect.');
insert into quotes values (608,'It is not possible to live in this age if you don’t have a sense of many contradictory forces.','Rem Koolhaas');
insert into quotes values (609,'I’m very accepting with my age. It’s like notches on your belt: experience, wisdom, and a different kind of beauty. There comes a day when you’ve become comfortable in your skin.','Zoe Saldana');
insert into quotes values (610,'You need some insecurity if you’re an actor. It keeps the pot boiling. I haven’t yet started to think about retiring. I was shocked when I heard about Paul Newman retiring at age 82. Most actors just fade away like old soldiers.','Al Pacino');
insert into quotes values (611,'It’s hard for women at my age in Hollywood, but I’m not discouraged.','Jane Fonda');
insert into quotes values (612,'We’re still living with the old paradigm of age as an arch. That’s the old metaphor: You’re born, you peak at midlife and decline into decrepitude.','Jane Fonda');
insert into quotes values (613,'We can no longer waste time and money. Every day, more than 2,000 girls in America, age 15-19, give birth','in the wealthiest, most educated nation in the world! Neither you nor I should accept this statistic.');
insert into quotes values (614,'The reality is sobering: in the United States one in three girls will become pregnant before age 20, totaling more than 750,000 girls per year.','Jane Fonda');
insert into quotes values (615,'I am hoping for peaceful transition into a new age. Obama has already played a great role in initiating us into that vision. If he were to be harmed in any way, it would spawn the birth of a million Obamas.','Saul Williams');
insert into quotes values (616,'I definitely don’t look my age. So I actively look for roles that will help people change their perception of me.','Elijah Wood');
insert into quotes values (617,'The age thing really bugs me. Do people have more of a right to not like what I say because I’m 19?','Fiona Apple');
insert into quotes values (618,'There are a lot of downsides to being male. We age faster and die younger. But give us this: we’re lifetime baby-making machines. Women’s reproductive abilities start to wane when they’re as young as 35. Men? We’re good to go pretty much till we’re dead.','Jeffrey Kluger');
insert into quotes values (619,'Older fatherhood isn’t all bad: testosterone rates drop about 1% per year as men age, making them less reactive and more patient, and a professionally established middle-aged man is likely to have more time and money to devote to his kids than a twenty-something who’s just getting started.','Jeffrey Kluger');
insert into quotes values (620,'Credit or debit cards, for starters, are nothing short of shoppers’ Novocain. Even in the age of digital purchases and virtual money, we still attach a special value to dirty paper with pictures of presidents on it. Handing some of that to a cashier simply hurts more than handing over a little sliver of plastic.','Jeffrey Kluger');
insert into quotes values (621,'When it comes to raising civilized kids there are no hard rules, but there are two things on which most parents agree: Boys are generally wilder than girls, and adolescents are wilder than kids of any other age. If you’ve got an adolescent boy, you’re in the sweet spot for trouble.','Jeffrey Kluger');
insert into quotes values (622,'It seems to me there is a change in what audiences want to see. I can only hope that’s correct, because there’s an awful lot of people of my age around now and we outnumber the others.','Maggie Smith');
insert into quotes values (623,'A truly great book should be read in youth, again in maturity and once more in old age, as a fine building should be seen by morning light, at noon and by moonlight.','Robertson Davies');
insert into quotes values (624,'In Hollywood, you play a mom, and the next thing you know, you’re on ‘The Golden Girls.’ They age you so fast.','Gabrielle Union');
insert into quotes values (625,'A great age of literature is perhaps always a great age of translations.','Ezra Pound');
insert into quotes values (626,'I can’t get my knickers in a twist about my age and ageing in an industry that caters to the ids of 14-year-olds.','Vera Farmiga');
insert into quotes values (627,'I was living on the wrong side of the tracks in Evanston, Illinois, in a home for boys. We had these Jackson 5 records. I really related to their voices','they were about my age, but they were doing it.');
insert into quotes values (628,'By age seven, I used to comb my hair for performances, just pull my hair up into a bun. Granted, it wasn’t a very intricate hairstyle. Still, to be that responsible and disciplined at age seven is unusual.','Janet Jackson');
insert into quotes values (629,'It begins and ends with money. It’s absurd in this day and age when we need so much money for education, health, for people, that a $100 million dollars can be spent on a film. It’s obscene.','Kathleen Turner');
insert into quotes values (630,'I am at that age when you panic at the slightest thing.','Rupert Everett');
insert into quotes values (631,'Being gay and being a woman has one big thing in common, which is that we both become invisible after the age of 42. Who wants a gay 50-year-old? No one, let me tell you.','Rupert Everett');
insert into quotes values (632,'I began to speak well at a very advanced age','15, 16, 17 years old. It was psychological: the trauma of war, my family and growing up on my own. I was more or less a street kid.');
insert into quotes values (633,'We Jews have a special attachment to the Book. The study of page after page in tomes yellowing with age was obligatory.','Theodore Bikel');
insert into quotes values (634,'Having come to live in this age is as though one were to have entered another country. Learn its language or risk being left out.','Theodore Bikel');
insert into quotes values (635,'I don’t want to look at other people my age in leather. Why would I put it on?','George Michael');
insert into quotes values (636,'I believe that the fight against crime starts in the home. Parents must take responsibility for their children and show them love and guidance from an early age so they learn to respect the rights of others.','Blanche Lincoln');
insert into quotes values (637,'At an early age, I started my own paper route. Once I saw how you could service people and do a good job and get paid for it, I just wanted to be the best I could be in whatever I did.','Puff Daddy');
insert into quotes values (638,'Middle age: when you begin to exchange your emotions for symptoms.','Irvin S. Cobb');
insert into quotes values (639,'Brain power improves by brain use, just as our bodily strength grows with exercise. And there is no doubt that a large proportion of the female population, from school days to late middle age, now have very complicated lives indeed.','A. N. Wilson');
insert into quotes values (640,'I began to understand my sensations, to know what I wanted, at around the age of forty','but only vaguely.');
insert into quotes values (641,'I grew up on a farm in a small town where you do or say one thing and everybody knows about it. You see it happen, there’s always the town gossip','‘Oh did you hear about so and so, or did you hear what went on in this household?’ So I learned at a very young age just to keep my mouth shut.');
insert into quotes values (642,'If you love somebody, you love them. My parents had a 25-year age gap between them and my mum was the breadwinner, my dad the house husband. I’m a strong believer that a good relationship can work, whatever the situation.','Katherine Jenkins');
insert into quotes values (643,'The Border Ballads, for instance, and the Robin Hood Ballads, clearly suppose a state of society which is nothing but a very circumscribed and not very important heroic age.','Lascelles Abercrombie');
insert into quotes values (644,'By the age of 9 or 10, I knew that I had to cut my own cloth and make my own way.','John le Carre');
insert into quotes values (645,'When you’re my age and you see a story, you better go for it pretty quickly. I’d just like to get a few more novels under my belt.','John le Carre');
insert into quotes values (646,'Catholics and evangelicals need to remain allied, and in solidarity, against the increasingly aggressive secularism of our age.','Gary Bauer');
insert into quotes values (647,'I don’t know whether it’s age or maturity, but I certainly find myself committed more and more to the looser forms of Western democracy at any price.','John le Carre');
insert into quotes values (648,'Losing both parents at a young age gave me a sense that you can’t really control life','so you’d better live it while it’s here. I stopped believing in a storybook existence a long time ago. All you can do is push in a direction and see what comes of it.');
insert into quotes values (649,'Old age is not a disease','it is strength and survivorship, triumph over all kinds of vicissitudes and disappointments, trials and illnesses.');
insert into quotes values (650,'I was a very sickly kid. While I was in the hospital at age 7, my Dad brought me a stack of comic books to keep me occupied. I was hooked.','Len Wein');
insert into quotes values (651,'Study until twenty-five, investigation until forty, profession until sixty, at which age I would have him retired on a double allowance.','Thomas Moore');
insert into quotes values (652,'In the digital age of ‘overnight’ success stories such as Facebook, the hard slog is easily overlooked.','James Dyson');
insert into quotes values (653,'The greatest writers of this age… are aware of the mystery of our existence.','J. B. Priestley');
insert into quotes values (654,'The chief role of the universities is to prolong adolescence into middle age, at which point early retirement ensures that we lack the means or the will to enforce significant change.','J. G. Ballard');
insert into quotes values (655,'My grandparents got married at a very young age, and a lot of what I think about marriage is based on their relationship. I watched them over the years and saw how they dealt with everything together, as a team.','Kyle Chandler');
insert into quotes values (656,'My grandparents got married at a very young age, and a lot of what I think about marriage is based on their relationship.','Kyle Chandler');
insert into quotes values (657,'At my age it is unseemly to be pessimistic.','Naguib Mahfouz');
insert into quotes values (658,'I don’t know why people are so obsessed with age anyway. I mean, 90 is the new 70 70 is the new 50 and 50 is the new 40 so the whole act-your-age thing? Only up to a point.','Joan Collins');
insert into quotes values (659,'I don’t look my age, I don’t feel my age and I don’t act my age. To me age is just a number.','Joan Collins');
insert into quotes values (660,'I believe that parents need to make nutrition education a priority in their home environment. It’s crucial for good health and longevity to instill in your children sound eating habits from an early age.','Cat Cora');
insert into quotes values (661,'Most poetry in the modern age has retreated to the private sphere, turning its back on the political realm.','Terry Eagleton');
insert into quotes values (662,'We incorporated new tastes and flavors into our kids’ diets from a very early age, which helped to develop their palates and prevented them from becoming picky eaters. We don’t buy junk food and give them options of fresh fruit, yogurt, raw almonds, or dried whole grain cereals for snack time.','Cat Cora');
insert into quotes values (663,'Filth and old age, I’m sure you will agree, are powerful wardens upon chastity.','Geoffrey Chaucer');
insert into quotes values (664,'It has been claimed at times that our modern age of technology facilitates dictatorship.','Henry A. Wallace');
insert into quotes values (665,'Working on the ‘Ice Age’ movies, I’m really proud to be in them.','Seann William Scott');
insert into quotes values (666,'No Congress ever has seen fit to amend the Constitution to address any issue related to marriage. No Constitutional Amendment was needed to ban polygamy or bigamy, nor was a Constitutional Amendment needed to set a uniform age of majority to ban child marriages.','Judy Biggert');
insert into quotes values (667,'We’re taught at such a young age that you can always be better and that you’re never perfect and that you’re never good enough.','Shawn Johnson');
insert into quotes values (668,'The young people have MTV and rock and roll. Why would they go to read poetry? Poetry belongs to the Stone Age. It awakens in us perceptions that go back to those times.','Robert Morgan');
insert into quotes values (669,'Study is the bane of childhood, the oil of youth, the indulgence of adulthood, and a restorative in old age.','Walter Savage Landor');
insert into quotes values (670,'Because of my age and because there’s more work on the small screen. What it’s missing in quality it makes up for in quantity. From an actor’s selfish point of view.','Cesar Romero');
insert into quotes values (671,'Old age is an insult. It’s like being smacked.','Lawrence Durrell');
insert into quotes values (672,'Age puzzles me. I thought it was a quiet time. My seventies were interesting and fairly serene, but my eighties are passionate. I grow more intense as I age.','Florida Scott-Maxwell');
insert into quotes values (673,'One of the great challenges of our age, in which the tools of our productivity are also the tools of our leisure, is to figure out how to make more useful those moments of procrastination when we’re idling in front of our computer screens.','Joshua Foer');
insert into quotes values (674,'I happen to be interested in watching a face age. I like faces of women aging so it makes me personally quite sad. That’s a beautiful gift from God. If people don’t want to see that anymore then I won’t be in anymore movies.','Debra Winger');
insert into quotes values (675,'Never say never, but the thought of electively cutting oneself is beyond my grasp, and I also object to it politically. Denying the lines on our faces makes a comment about age and wisdom I don’t care to make.','Debra Winger');
insert into quotes values (676,'People pay to see movies with women looking beautiful, but I think there will be a place for me to play women looking my own age.','Debra Winger');
insert into quotes values (677,'There’s a small club of women who are willing to age.','Debra Winger');
insert into quotes values (678,'I hope to find the roles that are age appropriate but not yearning to be younger, or parenting ad nauseam.','Debra Winger');
insert into quotes values (679,'I try to write lyrics so that they won’t age, which sort of leaves you with the big subjects like death and love and sex and violence.','Florence Welch');
insert into quotes values (680,'In the modern media age we are rarely surprised by what we see. Whether it’s on television or film or in the theatre, everything is so advertised, so trailed, that most entertainment is merely what you thought it was going to be like.','Rowan Atkinson');
insert into quotes values (681,'Your 40s are a major trough. About the age of 50, feelings of satisfaction begin to rebound and keep rising into your 50s, 60s and 70s, with health being a major factor.','Jane Pauley');
insert into quotes values (682,'I came back to work when my children were two months old. At that early age, they seem to have little awareness of anybody but their Raggedy Ann dolls, so it wasn’t a matter of them missing me. I was missing them.','Jane Pauley');
insert into quotes values (683,'Being successful at a very young age gave me the confidence and the capability to try out other things.','Joshua Lederberg');
insert into quotes values (684,'About the time I turned 50, I experienced the profound biological change that often accompanies women at that age. Also, I put two kids in college and lost both of my parents, so I’m no longer somebody’s daughter.','Jane Pauley');
insert into quotes values (685,'I feel more mature than most people my age.','Leighton Meester');
insert into quotes values (686,'Age does not bring you wisdom, age brings you wrinkles.','Estelle Getty');
insert into quotes values (687,'Maybe I’ll be a feminist in my old age.','Bjork');
insert into quotes values (688,'I feel the 21st century is another new age. Not only can we collaborate again with nature, but we have to. It’s an emergency.','Bjork');
insert into quotes values (689,'You can fake your age or mask it, but the passion that moves the characters has to be real.','Victoria Abril');
insert into quotes values (690,'I think that clearly it has an influence, to be coming of age during the punk rock era, to come from a difficult and sporadically violent background, to have been in and out of such chaos, I think it actually helps. But I don’t know for sure.','Craig Ferguson');
insert into quotes values (691,'I’d date someone younger or older age doesn’t matter to me. Or looks, really','it’s all about maturity.');
insert into quotes values (692,'Try to keep your soul young and quivering right up to old age.','George Sand');
insert into quotes values (693,'I wanted to be a forest ranger or a coal man. At a very early age, I knew I didn’t want to do what my dad did, which was work in an office.','Harrison Ford');
insert into quotes values (694,'Parenting is an impossible job at any age.','Harrison Ford');
insert into quotes values (695,'Sally Field looks amazing in general, never mind her age! She’s a phenomenally talented actress and has had a career spanning so many decades.','Alison Sweeney');
insert into quotes values (696,'I’ve had two romances since moving to Las Vegas. One was with somebody 12 years older than me, and the other was the same age, and neither worked out. I know people still think of me as one of Hugh Hefner’s girlfriends, and he of course was much older than me, but that was a whole different lifestyle and a different kind of dating.','Holly Madison');
insert into quotes values (697,'From age 16, I lived and breathed wine. I read every magazine and book about wine.','Gary Vaynerchuk');
insert into quotes values (698,'IQ is a commodity, data is a commodity. I’m far more interested in watching people interact at a restaurant with their smartphone. We can all read ‘Tech Crunch,’ ‘Ad Age.’ I would rather be living in the trenches. I would rather be going to Whole Foods in Columbus Circle to watch people shop with their smartphones.','Gary Vaynerchuk');
insert into quotes values (699,'Genius worship is the inevitable sign of an uncreative age.','Clive Bell');
insert into quotes values (700,'I appreciate and enjoy my age.','Nikki Giovanni');
insert into quotes values (701,'I’ve been going through photos of my mother, looking back on her life and trying to put it into context. Very few people age gracefully enough to be photographed through their aging.','Jamie Lee Curtis');
insert into quotes values (702,'I am rediscovering the whole sexual dimension of life at the age of 86, really. And that also means discovering the feminine. So the whole of this dimension, which I had been seeking for a very long time, is now sort of opening itself up to me.','Bede Griffiths');
insert into quotes values (703,'I think all writers of my age who are brought up on films probably by the age of 16 have seen many more films than they have read classics of literature. We can’t help but be influenced by film. Film has got some great tricks that it’s taught writers.','David Mitchell');
insert into quotes values (704,'Some broad themes brought me where I am today. At a very young age, my hobby became thinking and finding connections.','Dean Kamen');
insert into quotes values (705,'I think you have to be a little bit strict. You can’t be friend and their parent in a lot of situations, especially in this day and age where it’s so dangerous for kids. So there’s a bit of sternness, I guess, in the way I raise my kids.','Tim McGraw');
insert into quotes values (706,'In the 1970s and 1980s there was so little decent fiction for young people, but we’re now in a golden age that shows no sign of fading. Philip Pullman, J. K. Rowling, Lemony Snicket are only three of the best known among a good number of equals.','David Mitchell');
insert into quotes values (707,'I want to sell to people my own age, because that’s the way I write songs.','John Mellencamp');
insert into quotes values (708,'You get to a certain age and you just want to prove that you can still rock','that you’ve still got it.');
insert into quotes values (709,'I always thought that I might retire from any form of sexuality by the age of 40 and just become a dignified older person.','Jarvis Cocker');
insert into quotes values (710,'It’s only at this age that I can say the word ‘art’ without flinching.','Mira Nair');
insert into quotes values (711,'Well, once you’ve resigned yourself to the fact that you are the more mature pop performer and you’re past the age you ever thought you would do it, you might as well do it as long as you can. As long as I can still lift a microphone, then I’ll do it, you know.','Jarvis Cocker');
insert into quotes values (712,'I hope to have one more boxing match at the age of 55. Given that demographic at the age of 55 to 65, you’ve got to make a statement with your life. Otherwise, you are just existing.','George Foreman');
insert into quotes values (713,'I think it’s hard, the fact that there’s a certain age that we can’t have kids anymore.','Courteney Cox');
insert into quotes values (714,'While I had often said that I wanted to die in bed, what I really meant was that in my old age I wanted to be stepped on by an elephant while making love.','Roger Zelazny');
insert into quotes values (715,'I basically started playing violin at the age of six. That lasted about three years because my previous teacher died and the second teacher didn’t really know how to successfully get me going.','Miroslav Vitous');
insert into quotes values (716,'Age acquires no value save through thought and discipline.','James Truslow Adams');
insert into quotes values (717,'I’ve had to be a man since I was 12 or 13. I had a job. And I was playing the piano for people twice my age. Handling responsibility is what makes a man a man.','Jamie Foxx');
insert into quotes values (718,'Old age isn’t so bad when you consider the alternative.','Maurice Chevalier');
insert into quotes values (719,'Up until age 40, most men are just not as mature as women. So, it makes sense that a lot of women date up in age a bit.','Patti Stanger');
insert into quotes values (720,'Think back to yourself at age 18. I know I was mighty different than the Patti I am today. As we grow up, we grow out of our haircuts, our apartments and','often times');
insert into quotes values (721,'I was well motivated. What I wanted to do was work for myself. I had twenty two jobs before I started my business at the age of twenty three and I didn’t want one more boss telling me what to do. So I was motivated simply because I didn’t want a boss.','Barbara Corcoran');
insert into quotes values (722,'Regardless of age, regardless of position, regardless of the business we happen to be in, all of us need to understand the importance of branding. We are CEOs of our own companies: Me, Inc. To be in business today, our most important job is to be head marketer for the brand called You.','Tom Peters');
insert into quotes values (723,'An age which is incapable of poetry is incapable of any kind of literature except the cleverness of a decadence.','Raymond Chandler');
insert into quotes values (724,'I’ve always felt that sexuality is a really slippery thing. In this day and age, it tends to get categorized and labeled, and I think labels are for food. Canned food.','Michael Stipe');
insert into quotes values (725,'There must be a law against forcing children to perform at an early age. Children should have a wonderful childhood. They should not be given too much responsibility.','Maria Callas');
insert into quotes values (726,'Each age tries to form its own conception of the past. Each age writes the history of the past anew with reference to the conditions uppermost in its own time.','Frederick Jackson Turner');
insert into quotes values (727,'People quit on jobs. They quit on marriages. They quit on school. There’s an immediacy of this day and age that doesn’t lend itself to being committed to anything.','Emily Blunt');
insert into quotes values (728,'I nearly died of double bronchial pneumonia at the age of five.','Roger Moore');
insert into quotes values (729,'The wonderful thing about age is that your knees don’t work as well, you can’t run down steps quite as easily and obviously you can’t lift heavy weights. But your mind doesn’t feel any different.','Roger Moore');
insert into quotes values (730,'In a secular age, an authentic miracle must purport to be a hoax, in order to gain credit in the world.','Angela Carter');
insert into quotes values (731,'But I think it’s a little different in Europe, because 40 is really the best age for a woman. That’s when we hit our peak and become this ripe fruit.','Juliette Binoche');
insert into quotes values (732,'My mother was 45 when she had me, so when I was in high school my parents were the same age as my friends’ grandparents.','Jack White');
insert into quotes values (733,'In the age of television, image becomes more important than substance.','S. I. Hayakawa');
insert into quotes values (734,'Just call me a family man and an actor who digs his whole scene, side interests and all. Just say I feel mighty good at the ripe old age of 27.','Bobby Darin');
insert into quotes values (735,'Maybe back in the day you didn’t need to be the greatest looking to be on TV and you didn’t need to speak the best, but in this day and age, I think you need to be the package. You need to look the part for your sponsors, you need to be able to speak the part for the media and to big CEOs.','Danica Patrick');
insert into quotes values (736,'The culture of independent film criticism has totally gone down the drain and this seems to come with the territory of the consumer age that we are now living in.','Wim Wenders');
insert into quotes values (737,'There are only three things that can kill a farmer: lightning, rolling over in a tractor, and old age.','Bill Bryson');
insert into quotes values (738,'They say eyes clear with age.','Philip Larkin');
insert into quotes values (739,'Growing up on stage, I was introduced to makeup at a young age and I will never forget the first time I tried on a L’Oreal Paris iconic lipstick','it was instant glamour and I’ve been hooked ever since.');
insert into quotes values (740,'I don’t mind my age.','Heather Mills');
insert into quotes values (741,'Despite what anti-aging ads say, growing older can be better. I feel better in my skin, 100 percent. You have greater effects of gravity, but the better sense of yourself you have is something I wouldn’t trade. Women who lie about their age','‘why?’');
insert into quotes values (742,'For the moment I prefer to be a beautiful woman of my age than try desperately to look 30.','Demi Moore');
insert into quotes values (743,'It’s a little silly to finally learn how to write at this age. But I long ago realized I was secretly sincere.','Annie Dillard');
insert into quotes values (744,'It’s not always possible to sit down and eat at home in this day and age of fast-paced living, but if you are going to eat out, do so as a family and support all the great local places in your areas. I’ll still eat at the same diner I did as a kid with my parents.','Michael Symon');
insert into quotes values (745,'I worked hard in gymnastics since the time I was six years old until I retired at 23 years of age.','Nadia ComaneciYou may also like  180000 famous quotes part 63 - 62001 to 63000');
insert into quotes values (746,'I did successfully kick tobacco at the age of 34. I smoked for like 20 years, from 14 to 34.','Larry Hagman');
insert into quotes values (747,'India saw from the beginning, and, even in her ages of reason and her age of increasing ignorance, she never lost hold of the insight, that life cannot be rightly seen in the sole light, cannot be perfectly lived in the sole power of its externalities.','Sri Aurobindo');
insert into quotes values (748,'Back in the 1960s, I saw Peter, Paul and Mary. I was at that age, about 14, and I was mesmerized.','Lucinda Williams');
insert into quotes values (749,'For me from a pretty young age up until about 21 years old hallucinogenics had a huge place in my life.','Jon Fishman');
insert into quotes values (750,'A sense of freedom is something that, happily, comes with age and life experience.','Diane Keaton');
insert into quotes values (751,'Writers obviously have to bear witness to the harsh face of the age.','Alexander McCall Smith');
insert into quotes values (752,'Stop living a day at a time and stop worrying about age.','Helen Reddy');
insert into quotes values (753,'Young women from a very young age are taught that life will be easier if you can just turn on the charming smile and say very little and be complacent and docile and sweet.','Amber Heard');
insert into quotes values (754,'I started writing when I had three kids under the age of 4. I used to write every ten minutes I got to sit in front of a computer. Now, when I have more time, I function the same way: if it’s writing time, I write.','Jodi Picoult');
insert into quotes values (755,'I’m never overawed by a situation and I think that’s because I’ve always looked several years older than I am. So because people were treating me like I was 40 when I was 29, I’ve always felt in control of a situation. People used to say, when you’re 32, you’ll look 32. I’m still waiting for that moment, where my age catches up with my appearance.','Chris O’Dowd');
insert into quotes values (756,'I am 54 and age is slowly writing itself on my face.','Arthur Smith');
insert into quotes values (757,'I envy the sensibility in Europe, appreciating beauty in women as they age. I’m going to go that way. I might dye my gray hair for a bit, but beyond that the buck stops. I’m not having any work done.','Rachel Bilson');
insert into quotes values (758,'It was Julie Burchill who decreed that, beyond a certain age, a man should not be seen in a leather jacket.','Arthur Smith');
insert into quotes values (759,'As a result of the digital age and the decline of first-class mail, there is no question that the Postal Service must change and develop a new business model.','Bernie Sanders');
insert into quotes values (760,'I’ve watched my peers get better with age and hoped that would happen with me.','Bonnie Raitt');
insert into quotes values (761,'I never wanted to do TV. I just did what I was trained to do through the Special Forces, and I’ve been doing that from a very young age.','Bear Grylls');
insert into quotes values (762,'Here’s a proposal, offered only partly in jest: no resident of the United States, whether born here or abroad, should get to be a citizen until age 18, at which time each such resident has to take a test.','Eric Liu');
insert into quotes values (763,'Second to agriculture, humbug is the biggest industry of our age.','Alfred Nobel');
insert into quotes values (764,'When it comes down to it, it’s about who you know, and who’s a fan. It’s about whether you’re the right age, whether you’re hot or not, whether the studio is into you or not.','Marlee Matlin');
insert into quotes values (765,'Another principle is, the deepest affections of our hearts gather around some human form in which are incarnated the living thoughts and ideas of the passing age.','Matthew Simpson');
insert into quotes values (766,'My acting career began at age three and my parents got me into it. I was in a McDonald’s commercial.','Corey Feldman');
insert into quotes values (767,'I think that age as a number is not nearly as important as health. You can be in poor health and be pretty miserable at 40 or 50. If you’re in good health, you can enjoy things into your 80s.','Bob Barker');
insert into quotes values (768,'I just yesterday returned from a trip where I photographed a woman with two children whom I photographed first when she was the age of the older of the two children.','Jock Sturges');
insert into quotes values (769,'You live in a deranged age, more deranged that usual, because in spite of great scientific and technological advances, man has not the faintest idea of who he is or what he is doing.','Walker Percy');
insert into quotes values (770,'To write a story about New York that only deals with people in your age and socioeconomic bracket, that feels dishonest to me. So much of New York comes from everyone bumping into each other.','Josh Radnor');
insert into quotes values (771,'My mother inspired me to treat others as I would want to be treated regardless of age, race or financial status.','Tommy Hilfiger');
insert into quotes values (772,'And from the first time I picked up a basketball at age eight','I had a lot of difficulty when I first picked up a basketball, because I was a scrub');
insert into quotes values (773,'Right up until the time I retired at age 37, I felt like there were still things that I could do better.','Julius Erving');
insert into quotes values (774,'In 1981, at age 31, I was voted the best player in basketball, and the most valuable player in the league.','Julius Erving');
insert into quotes values (775,'The great thing about arriving at this age is that I don’t even care about my career anymore.','Ron Perlman');
insert into quotes values (776,'Almost all of your life is lived by the seat of your pants, one unexpected event crashing into another, with no pattern or reason, and then you finally reach a point, around my age, where you spend more time than ever looking back. Why did this happen? Look where that led? You see the shape of things.','Ron Perlman');
insert into quotes values (777,'I’ve always been intrigued by color and by interesting hair. I was one of those weird little girls doing my own hair at the age of 9. I was, like, getting weird gels and new brushes and cornrow holders. I would tweak and perm at the age of 13.','Nicki Minaj');
insert into quotes values (778,'There are no college courses to build up self-esteem or high school or elementary school. If you don’t get those values at a early age, nurtured in your home, you don’t get them.','T. D. Jakes');
insert into quotes values (779,'The freethinking of one age is the common sense of the next.','Matthew Arnold');
insert into quotes values (780,'If children are not introduced to music at an early age, I believe something fundamental is actually being taken from them.','Luciano Pavarotti');
insert into quotes values (781,'Middle age is when your broad mind and narrow waist begin to change places.','E. Joseph Cossman');
insert into quotes values (782,'As an American, you have a right to good health care that is effective, accessible, and affordable, that serves you from infancy through old age, that allows you to go to practitioners and facilities of your choosing, and that offers a broad range of therapeutic options.','Andrew Weil');
insert into quotes values (783,'Women would be disproportionately affected by the privatization of social security. It is one of the most important safety nets for American women in old age, or in times of disability, to insure financial income for their families.','Barbara Mikulski');
insert into quotes values (784,'Low levels of vitamin D in the population as a whole suggest that most people need to take a vitamin D supplement. This may be especially true for seniors, as the ability to synthesize vitamin D in the skin declines with age.','Andrew Weil');
insert into quotes values (785,'Part of the reason I sort of shot out like a cannon out of Michigan and left home at such an early age is because I had to feel independent.','Madonna Ciccone');
insert into quotes values (786,'I think that everyone at any age should ask themselves, ‘where do I want to be today, where do I want to be tomorrow, and where do I want to be in a hundred years?’ We all have clear answers to those questions. We only have so much time. It’s a real shame if we don’t spend our lives trying to do that.','Jack Antonoff');
insert into quotes values (787,'My parents got married late and they had kids late, so I never felt a social or cultural thing to be married or pregnant or a homeowner by a certain age.','Anna Kendrick');
insert into quotes values (788,'I’m a pretty big dork. It’s crazy. I’m one of those people who grew up with all kinds of musicals, but I was right at that age where ‘Rent’ was a big deal for me and for my friends.','Anna Kendrick');
insert into quotes values (789,'My parents were really, really cool about supporting what I wanted to do at a really young age. I think I was about 10 when I caught the bug. They would drive me down to New York if there were auditions. When I was 12, I did this show on Broadway called ‘High Society,’ so we moved to New York for the run of that.','Anna Kendrick');
insert into quotes values (790,'I was very sexual from a very young age.','Portia de Rossi');
insert into quotes values (791,'It is a sobering thought that when Mozart was my age, he had been dead for two years.','Tom Lehrer');
insert into quotes values (792,'And I’m not as young as I once was. At my age, I don’t have time to be bored.','Lev Grossman');
insert into quotes values (793,'I was drafted into the Army when I was 19 and came out at age 22. Most people that I knew didn’t think they’d come home alive. I didn’t think I would either, so I was happy when I did.','Ed Koch');
insert into quotes values (794,'One already feels like an anachronism, writing novels in the age of what-ever-this-is-the-age-of, but touring to promote them feels doubly anachronistic. The marketplace is showing an increasing intolerance for the time-honored practice of printing information on paper and shipping it around the country.','Lev Grossman');
insert into quotes values (795,'To own the dominant, or only, newspaper in a mid-sized American city was, for many decades, a kind of license to print money. In the Internet age, however, no one has figured out how to rescue the newspaper in the United States or abroad.','Eric Alterman');
insert into quotes values (796,'I grew up loving horses. I was relatively obsessed, starting with my rocking horse at age 2, all the way through my painting and drawing phase.','Diane Lane');
insert into quotes values (797,'I was equally in love with singing and acting from an early age.','Minnie Driver');
insert into quotes values (798,'You can construct the character of a man and his age not only from what he does and says, but from what he fails to say and do.','Norman Douglas');
insert into quotes values (799,'I never played much golf as a kid. I caddied quite a bit but never got serious into golf until about age 15.','Lee Trevino');
insert into quotes values (800,'These days too many of us seem inclined to cover our ears, close our eyes, and blindly follow the most narrow, conservative tenets of religion or else seek comfort in the ancient traditions of New Age ritual.','Joan D. Vinge');
insert into quotes values (801,'There is no age, height, or weight requirement to skate. It is good exercise no matter what your age is. If you want to be competitive, most start young. But, I practice with many adult competitors.','Nancy Kerrigan');
insert into quotes values (802,'I remember when I was 6 years old and my brother used to go seek out guys that were 13 to come over and play football against me while he was the ‘permanent quarterback.’ I didn’t know exactly what the age difference was, but I was already playing against older guys.','Junior Seau');
insert into quotes values (803,'Well, my son really loves wildlife. And everytime he draws a polar bear I want to tell him there probably won’t any by the time… he’s my age. That’s kinda hard to deal with.','Thom Yorke');
insert into quotes values (804,'To be perfectly honest, I think that as I’m growing older, I’m just growing more impatient. I’ll be very happy if at some point people say, ‘Michael’s grown wiser and softer in his old age.’ But we’ll have to wait and see what my next project is.','Michael Haneke');
insert into quotes values (805,'A woman my age is not supposed to be attractive or sexually appealing. I just get kinda tired of that.','Kathleen Turner');
insert into quotes values (806,'Listen, in England people are already writing their memoirs at the age of 23.','Rupert Everett');
insert into quotes values (807,'I was apprehensive. I feared every time I talked about poetry, it would be filtered through the lens of race, sex, and age.','Rita Dove');
insert into quotes values (808,'Everyone takes pause at 40. It’s the age you have to assess everything in your life. It’s the fictitious marker that’s always coming up when you’re young. The world really does look at you to kind of have it together by 40, and be successful by 40. Whatever success means.','Paul Feig');
insert into quotes values (809,'I started out modeling at a young age and surrounded myself with different brilliant minds. I have so many people to get educated from, and I’ve been a sponge.','Kellan Lutz');
insert into quotes values (810,'People say women shouldn’t have long hair over a certain age, but I’ve never done what everyone says.','Jane Seymour');
insert into quotes values (811,'We tend to think of age only in time, but I don’t think it has much to do with time at all there’s a whole load of other things. I’ve met 16-year-olds who are old and 90-year-olds who are young.','Roger Daltrey');
insert into quotes values (812,'It looks good when you see someone kicking at the age of 51 with no double. It’s kinda cool for people to know that past 50 we can keep flexible.','Jean Claude Van Damme');
insert into quotes values (813,'The second album was emotionally exhausting and my life felt like it had become very serious at a very young age.','Delta Goodrem');
insert into quotes values (814,'I never felt totally, 100%, patriotically English… I’d seen a lot of the world by an early age','sort of spent a lot of time traveling around Lebanon and I’d seen Babylon, and Damascus, and all sorts of places in the Middle East by the time I was ten. Then we’d return to Ruslip in West London… Done a fair bit of traveling really.');
insert into quotes values (815,'The first feminine feature that goes, with advancing age, is the neck.','Gloria Swanson');
insert into quotes values (816,'You just never know when you’re living in a golden age.','Alexander Payne');
insert into quotes values (817,'We now have an opportunity, though, to do something we didn’t do in the industrial age, and that is to get a leg up on this, to bring the public in quickly, to have an informed debate.','Jeremy Rifkin');
insert into quotes values (818,'I’ve spent as much as 30 grand on a watch but it’s not about flaunting my wealth. I don’t have many extravagances but watches are my biggest one. I must have 30 of them now. I’ve been collecting since the age of nine, when I won a black TAG in a karting event.','Jenson Button');
insert into quotes values (819,'We were making the first step out of the age of chemistry and physics, and into the age of biology.','Jeremy Rifkin');
insert into quotes values (820,'I feel like women are asked their age more than men.','Kristen Wiig');
insert into quotes values (821,'Even in this day and age, if you’re not married, there are people who are like, ‘Awww! Don’t worry, it’ll happen for you someday.’','Kristen Wiig');
insert into quotes values (822,'For students today, only 10 percent of children from working-class families graduate from college by the age of 24 as compared to 58 percent of upper-middle-class and wealthy families.','Patrick J. Kennedy');
insert into quotes values (823,'I have worked very hard on being aware of my childhood but moving forward and not letting it bring me down emotionally. That is a hard thing','especially when you have children of your own and you remember what happened to you at that age.');
insert into quotes values (824,'Traveling to Russia and Germany and being able to see the world at a young age was really cool for me, and I really liked that.','Mia Wasikowska');
insert into quotes values (825,'I vividly remember being 14. That was the age when I started to get happy: I started being a writer and stopped being a loser.','Anthony Horowitz');
insert into quotes values (826,'The balance of private good and general welfare is at the bottom of civilized morals but the morals of the Heroic Age are founded on individuality, and on nothing else.','Lascelles Abercrombie');
insert into quotes values (827,'I also find it interesting that a lot of people in their 30s are not married and don’t have kids. There are a lot of people in this age bracket that are out there dating and trying to find love. And I never thought that at my age I would be.','John Stamos');
insert into quotes values (828,'The reason can only be this: heroic poetry depends on an heroic age, and an age is heroic because of what it is, not because of what it does.','Lascelles Abercrombie');
insert into quotes values (829,'The 19th century was the age of Individualism the 20th and 21st are the ages of Socialism.','Francis Parker Yockey');
insert into quotes values (830,'We live in an age of mediocrity.','Lauren Bacall');
insert into quotes values (831,'I gambled and I lost. I failed in securing my options for this choice for myself, but I succeeded in verifying the Dark Age is still with us.','Jack Kevorkian');
insert into quotes values (832,'I always looked really young for my age. And once I hit 23, 24 and 25, I was then allowed to play the cool 18-year-olds and stuff.','Ben Barnes');
insert into quotes values (833,'I want to be age appropriate. I don’t want to be that girl you see walking away and she looks 25 and then she turns around and she looks 90.','Stevie Nicks');
insert into quotes values (834,'When I was at school, I was in choirs more than anything else, from a very young age, about 9 years old. And then I started taking drum lessons.','Ben Barnes');
insert into quotes values (835,'I was always obsessed with being famous. I had Marilyn Monroe paper dolls as a child, and I was always obsessed with her. I’ve just been really driven in that direction, and none of my friends were. So, I don’t know what put that bug in me at a young age.','Holly Madison');
insert into quotes values (836,'All my early school reports from the age of 5 were ‘Daniel must learn not to distract others.’','Dan Stevens');
insert into quotes values (837,'At the age of 11 I was about 6 ft. tall and my voice had completely broken. That caused problems. I was this gangly, spotty, very unattractive kid. I wasn’t cool and I wasn’t a nerd. I didn’t even want to fit in with anyone.','Dan Stevens');
insert into quotes values (838,'I’ve always tried to do my very best, and I want to be the very best age, whatever age I am.','Ann-Margret');
insert into quotes values (839,'I never quite toed the line. I was a bit disruptive. All my early school reports from the age of 5 were ‘Daniel must learn not to distract others.’ And now, that’s what I do for a living.','Dan Stevens');
insert into quotes values (840,'One problem with age is that patience begins to ebb.','Carl Hiaasen');
insert into quotes values (841,'Men of my age live in a state of continual desperation.','Vita Sackville-West');
insert into quotes values (842,'Starting a new retirement plan for those below a certain age is something tens of millions of Americans have already been through at work.','Mitch Daniels');
insert into quotes values (843,'Anybody under the age of forty knows hip-hop, gospel and R&ampB pretty well, and it’s all a part of what we consider to be ‘black music.’ There is a natural synergy between the three.','John Legend');
insert into quotes values (844,'Well, Jeff Buckley for me is one of the greatest singers I’ve ever heard. And the reason why is he has an amazing range, amazing emotional power in his voice. And the music he put around it also just had this passion and this soul to it and this spirit to it that very few artists have, and he passed at a very young age.','John Legend');
insert into quotes values (845,'It’s getting better generally, daily, especially in TV, for women in acting and age and looks count less. As more women come into the business. Change of any sort takes a long time to happen.','Julie Walters');
insert into quotes values (846,'I think the most exciting thing is that you expect people our age to know the music, but actually a lot of kids know the music, and if anything is left, we have left really good music, and that’s the important part, not the mop-tops or whatever.','Ringo Starr');
insert into quotes values (847,'It doesn’t matter what color, sex, religion, age, sexual orientation, etc., everyone should have the same freedoms and liberties.','Lance Bass');
insert into quotes values (848,'Childhood itself is scarcely more lovely than a cheerful, kindly, sunshiny old age.','Lydia M. Child');
insert into quotes values (849,'In my older age, I’ve learned to take things slower, because I used to be that total-fall-in-love-after-a-day guy.','Lance Bass');
insert into quotes values (850,'You watch yourself age and it’s hard to feel like a sex symbol.','Idris Elba');
insert into quotes values (851,'I like to be alone so I can write. But focus can hurt you. I don’t want to be some stress casualty in early middle age.','James Ellroy');
insert into quotes values (852,'I’d always thought the Rats were good fun, but one of the very nice things about being of Saga age is that I can actually look back and think, When I was younger I was in a great band. It was always a collective thing.','Bob Geldof');
insert into quotes values (853,'I do think I feel it but you don’t think you are cause at a certain time you are no age but you don’t think you are anything. You feel the life you have lived. I feel that. It’s been a long fifty years.','Bob Geldof');
insert into quotes values (854,'The crucial task of old age is balance: keeping just well enough, just brave enough, just gay and interested and starkly honest enough to remain a sentient human being.','Florida Scott-Maxwell');
insert into quotes values (855,'My first job was in retail at the age of 14, and I have worked in the industry ever since.','Rachel Roy');
insert into quotes values (856,'I believed my story would be helpful to young women my daughter’s age, who are still in the process of forming themselves as women, and in need of encouragement to remain true to themselves.','Joyce Maynard');
insert into quotes values (857,'Old age and sickness bring out the essential characteristics of a man.','Felix Frankfurter');
insert into quotes values (858,'We hold that the most wonderful and splendid proof of genius is a great poem produced in a civilized age.','Thomas B. Macaulay');
insert into quotes values (859,'The age we live in is a busy age in which knowledge is rapidly advancing towards perfection.','Jeremy Bentham');
insert into quotes values (860,'In a spiritually sensitive culture, then, it might well be that age is something to be admired or envied.','Rowan D. Williams');
insert into quotes values (861,'What though youth gave love and roses, Age still leaves us friends and wine.','Thomas More');
insert into quotes values (862,'If there is anything I would do differently in my life, it is that I would study business more. I’m trying to teach my daughter Chloe at an early age about investing and money so she’s not afraid of it.','Donna Mills');
insert into quotes values (863,'Any young man who is unmarried at the age of twenty one is a menace to the community.','Brigham Young');
insert into quotes values (864,'Time, in general, has always been a central obsession of mine','what it does to people, how it can constitute a plot all on its own. So naturally, I am interested in old age.');
insert into quotes values (865,'The first crocodile I ever caught was at nine years of age, and it was a rescue.','Steve Irwin');
insert into quotes values (866,'It is strange to be known so universally and yet to be so lonely.','Albert Einstein');
insert into quotes values (867,'Alone we can do so little together we can do so much.','Helen Keller');
insert into quotes values (868,'It’s often just enough to be with someone. I don’t need to touch them. Not even talk. A feeling passes between you both. You’re not alone.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (869,'Associate with men of good quality if you esteem your own reputation for it is better to be alone than in bad company.','George Washington');
insert into quotes values (870,'I restore myself when I’m alone.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (871,'A man is born alone and dies alone and he experiences the good and bad consequences of his karma alone and he goes alone to hell or the Supreme abode.','Chanakya');
insert into quotes values (872,'I have to be alone very often. I’d be quite happy if I spent from Saturday night until Monday morning alone in my apartment. That’s how I refuel.','Audrey Hepburn');
insert into quotes values (873,'I don’t want to be alone, I want to be left alone.','Audrey Hepburn');
insert into quotes values (874,'You cannot be lonely if you like the person you’re alone with.','Wayne Dyer');
insert into quotes values (875,'We allow our ignorance to prevail upon us and make us think we can survive alone, alone in patches, alone in groups, alone in races, even alone in genders.','Maya Angelou');
insert into quotes values (876,'If it’s true that our species is alone in the universe, then I’d have to say the universe aimed rather low and settled for very little.','George Carlin');
insert into quotes values (877,'Language… has created the word ‘loneliness’ to express the pain of being alone. And it has created the word ‘solitude’ to express the glory of being alone.','Paul Tillich');
insert into quotes values (878,'I love to be alone. I never found the companion that was so companionable as solitude.','Henry David Thoreau');
insert into quotes values (879,'Look at the sky. We are not alone. The whole universe is friendly to us and conspires only to give the best to those who dream and work.','Abdul Kalam');
insert into quotes values (880,'Every man must do two things alone he must do his own believing and his own dying.','Martin Luther');
insert into quotes values (881,'Loneliness is my least favorite thing about life. The thing that I’m most worried about is just being alone without anybody to care for or someone who will care for me.','Anne Hathaway');
insert into quotes values (882,'I have never found a companion that was so companionable as solitude. We are for the most part more lonely when we go abroad among men than when we stay in our chambers. A man thinking or working is always alone, let him be where he will.','Henry David Thoreau');
insert into quotes values (883,'I finally faced the fact that it isn’t a crime not having friends. Being alone means you have fewer problems.','Whitney Houston');
insert into quotes values (884,'Yes, I guess you could say I am a loner, but I feel more lonely in a crowed room with boring people than I feel on my own.','Henry Rollins');
insert into quotes values (885,'The only real progress lies in learning to be wrong all alone.','Albert Camus');
insert into quotes values (886,'If you are lonely when you’re alone, you are in bad company.','Jean-Paul Sartre');
insert into quotes values (887,'Life could be wonderful if people would leave you alone.','Charlie Chaplin');
insert into quotes values (888,'All men’s miseries derive from not being able to sit in a quiet room alone.','Blaise Pascal');
insert into quotes values (889,'We are rarely proud when we are alone.','Voltaire');
insert into quotes values (890,'We are all sentenced to solitary confinement inside our own skins, for life.','Tennessee Williams');
insert into quotes values (891,'It’s an interesting combination: Having a great fear of being alone, and having a desperate need for solitude and the solitary experience. That’s always been a tug of war for me.','Jodie Foster');
insert into quotes values (892,'Unlike a drop of water which loses its identity when it joins the ocean, man does not lose his being in the society in which he lives. Man’s life is independent. He is born not for the development of the society alone, but for the development of his self.','B. R. Ambedkar');
insert into quotes values (893,'If I am a legend, then why am I so lonely?','Judy Garland');
insert into quotes values (894,'A man can be himself only so long as he is alone.','Arthur Schopenhauer');
insert into quotes values (895,'What a lovely surprise to finally discover how unlonely being alone can be.','Ellen Burstyn');
insert into quotes values (896,'Still and all, why bother? Here’s my answer. Many people need desperately to receive this message: I feel and think much as you do, care about many of the things you care about, although most people do not care about them. You are not alone.','Kurt Vonnegut');
insert into quotes values (897,'When so many are lonely as seem to be lonely, it would be inexcusably selfish to be lonely alone.','Tennessee Williams');
insert into quotes values (898,'You come into the world alone and you go out of the world alone yet it seems to me you are more alone while living than even going and coming.','Emily Carr');
insert into quotes values (899,'To live alone is the fate of all great souls.','Arthur Schopenhauer');
insert into quotes values (900,'The time you feel lonely is the time you most need to be by yourself.','Doug Coupland');
insert into quotes values (901,'I’ve also seen that great men are often lonely. This is understandable, because they have built such high standards for themselves that they often feel alone. But that same loneliness is part of their ability to create.','Yousuf Karsh');
insert into quotes values (902,'In Genesis, it says that it is not good for a man to be alone but sometimes it is a great relief.','John Barrymore');
insert into quotes values (903,'I only go out to get me a fresh appetite for being alone.','Lord Byron');
insert into quotes values (904,'The lonely become either thoughtful or empty.','Mason Cooley');
insert into quotes values (905,'There’s a tremendous difference between alone and lonely. You could be lonely in a group of people. I like being alone. I like eating by myself. I go home at night and just watch a movie or hang out with my dog. I have to exert myself and really say, oh God, I’ve got to see my friends ’cause I’m too content being by myself.','Drew Barrymore');
insert into quotes values (906,'I really enjoy being single again. I spent a lot of time in a relationship and the nearer we came to the end, the more difficult it got. You don’t see things clearly as long as you’re still involved.','Dido Armstrong');
insert into quotes values (907,'The best part about being alone is that you really don’t have to answer to anybody. You do what you want.','Justin Timberlake');
insert into quotes values (908,'The desire to get married, which','I regret to say, I believe is basic and primal in women');
insert into quotes values (909,'Who knows what true loneliness is','not the conventional word but the naked terror? To the lonely themselves it wears a mask. The most miserable outcast hugs some memory or some illusion.');
insert into quotes values (910,'Living alone makes it harder to find someone to blame.','Mason Cooley');
insert into quotes values (911,'As a body everyone is single, as a soul never.','Hermann Hesse');
insert into quotes values (912,'The capacity for not feeling lonely can carry a very real price, that of feeling nothing at all.','Doug Coupland');
insert into quotes values (913,'Always give a word or sign of salute when meeting or passing a friend, or even a stranger, if in a lonely place.','Tecumseh');
insert into quotes values (914,'All men’s misfortunes spring from their hatred of being alone.','Jean de la Bruyere');
insert into quotes values (915,'To dare to live alone is the rarest courage since there are many who had rather meet their bitterest enemy in the field, than their own hearts in their closet.','Charles Caleb Colton');
insert into quotes values (916,'Even in the presence of others he was completely alone.','Robert M. Pirsig');
insert into quotes values (917,'Alone let him constantly meditate in solitude on that which is salutary for his soul, for he who meditates in solitude attains supreme bliss.','Guru Nanak');
insert into quotes values (918,'I have so many different personalities in me and I still feel lonely.','Tori Amos');
insert into quotes values (919,'I never said, ‘I want to be alone.’ I only said, ‘I want to be left alone.’ There is all the difference.','Greta Garbo');
insert into quotes values (920,'Every man is born as many men and dies as a single one.','Martin Heidegger');
insert into quotes values (921,'I paint self-portraits because I am so often alone, because I am the person I know best.','Frida Kahlo');
insert into quotes values (922,'As I get older I’m more and more comfortable being alone.','Sienna Miller');
insert into quotes values (923,'I’m fascinated with myself and love hearing the sound of my own voice. I’d like to hear what I have to say. A lot of people don’t like being alone because they truly don’t like themselves, but I love me.','Gene Simmons');
insert into quotes values (924,'I would be married, but I’d have no wife, I would be married to a single life.','Charles Bukowski');
insert into quotes values (925,'Unless we love and are loved, each of us is alone, each of us is deeply lonely.','Mortimer Adler');
insert into quotes values (926,'A man content to go to heaven alone will never go to heaven.','Boethius');
insert into quotes values (927,'He that can live alone resembles the brute beast in nothing, the sage in much, and God in everything.','Baltasar Gracian');
insert into quotes values (928,'Remember we’re all in this alone.','Lily Tomlin');
insert into quotes values (929,'Solitude is the profoundest fact of the human condition. Man is the only being who knows he is alone.','Octavio Paz');
insert into quotes values (930,'Absolutely lonely people have few personal interactions of any kind.','Martha Beck');
insert into quotes values (931,'Is he alone who has courage on his right hand and faith on his left hand?','Charles Lindbergh');
insert into quotes values (932,'Don’t go away. I don’t want to be alone. I can’t stand being alone.','Arnold Rothstein');
insert into quotes values (933,'Inside myself is a place where I live all alone and that is where I renew my springs that never dry up.','Pearl S. Buck');
insert into quotes values (934,'Being alone is very difficult.','Yoko Ono');
insert into quotes values (935,'I would rather be a beggar and single than a queen and married.','Elizabeth I');
insert into quotes values (936,'If you make friends with yourself you will never be alone.','Maxwell Maltz');
insert into quotes values (937,'Only the lonely know the way I feel tonight.','Roy Orbison');
insert into quotes values (938,'Be able to be alone. Lose not the advantage of solitude, and the society of thyself.','Thomas Browne');
insert into quotes values (939,'The longer one is alone, the easier it is to hear the song of the earth.','Robert Anton Wilson');
insert into quotes values (940,'All of our unhappiness comes from our inability to be alone.','Jean de la Bruyere');
insert into quotes values (941,'When the people you love are gone, you’re alone.','Keanu Reeves');
insert into quotes values (942,'You can’t fake it when you’re alone with God, you know.','Jim Bakker');
insert into quotes values (943,'Nothing makes us so lonely as our secrets.','Paul Tournier');
insert into quotes values (944,'If you’re going to put yourself above everybody else, you might end up alone.','Joseph Gordon-Levitt');
insert into quotes values (945,'By all means use some time to be alone.','Edward Young');
insert into quotes values (946,'I think I jump around more when I’m alone.','Nicolas Cage');
insert into quotes values (947,'When I’m alone, I can sleep crossways in bed without an argument.','Zsa Zsa Gabor');
insert into quotes values (948,'There are places and moments in which one is so completely alone that one sees the world entire.','Jules Renard');
insert into quotes values (949,'I’m happily single.','Paula Abdul');
insert into quotes values (950,'You’re only lonely if you’re not there for you.','Phil McGraw');
insert into quotes values (951,'I’m single, footloose and fancy free, I have no responsibilities, no anchors. Work, friendship and self-improvement, that’s me.','Joel Edgerton');
insert into quotes values (952,'When everything is lonely I can be my best friend.','Conor Oberst');
insert into quotes values (953,'A human being is a single being. Unique and unrepeatable.','Eileen Caddy');
insert into quotes values (954,'Your actions, and your action alone, determines your worth.','Evelyn Waugh');
insert into quotes values (955,'I think the greatest amount of pressure is the pressure I place on myself. So in a way I chose to be alone.','Cathy Freeman');
insert into quotes values (956,'You only grow when you are alone.','Paul Newman');
insert into quotes values (957,'We’re born alone, we live alone, we die alone. Only through our love and friendship can we create the illusion for the moment that we’re not alone.','Orson Welles');
insert into quotes values (958,'For beautiful eyes, look for the good in others for beautiful lips, speak only words of kindness and for poise, walk with the knowledge that you are never alone.','Audrey Hepburn');
insert into quotes values (959,'Take up one idea. Make that one idea your life','think of it, dream of it, live on that idea. Let the brain, muscles, nerves, every part of your body, be full of that idea, and just leave every other idea alone. This is the way to success.');
insert into quotes values (960,'Walking with a friend in the dark is better than walking alone in the light.','Helen Keller');
insert into quotes values (961,'Before the throne of the Almighty, man will be judged not by his acts but by his intentions. For God alone reads our hearts.','Mahatma Gandhi');
insert into quotes values (962,'It’s better to be unhappy alone than unhappy with someone','so far.');
insert into quotes values (963,'Love is our true destiny. We do not find the meaning of life by ourselves alone','we find it with another.');
insert into quotes values (964,'Nothing in this world can take the place of persistence. Talent will not nothing is more common than unsuccessful people with talent. Genius will not unrewarded genius is almost a proverb. Education will not the world is full of educated failures. Persistence and determination alone are omnipotent.','Calvin Coolidge');
insert into quotes values (965,'I may climb perhaps to no great heights, but I will climb alone.','Cyrano de Bergerac');
insert into quotes values (966,'What we have done for ourselves alone dies with us what we have done for others and the world remains and is immortal.','Albert Pike');
insert into quotes values (967,'I am free because I know that I alone am morally responsible for everything I do. I am free, no matter what rules surround me. If I find them tolerable, I tolerate them if I find them too obnoxious, I break them. I am free because I know that I alone am morally responsible for everything I do.','Robert A. Heinlein');
insert into quotes values (968,'We can be tired, weary and emotionally distraught, but after spending time alone with God, we find that He injects into our bodies energy, power and strength.','Charles Stanley');
insert into quotes values (969,'Every government degenerates when trusted to the rulers of the people alone. The people themselves are its only safe depositories.','Thomas Jefferson');
insert into quotes values (970,'It is error alone which needs the support of government. Truth can stand by itself.','Thomas Jefferson');
insert into quotes values (971,'The best remedy for those who are afraid, lonely or unhappy is to go outside, somewhere where they can be quiet, alone with the heavens, nature and God. Because only then does one feel that all is as it should be.','Anne Frank');
insert into quotes values (972,'The hours I spend with you I look upon as sort of a perfumed garden, a dim twilight, and a fountain singing to it. You and you alone make me feel that I am alive. Other men it is said have seen angels, but I have seen thee and thou art enough.','George Edward Moore');
insert into quotes values (973,'Our Lord has written the promise of resurrection, not in books alone, but in every leaf in springtime.','Martin Luther');
insert into quotes values (974,'I think this is the most extraordinary collection of talent, of human knowledge, that has ever been gathered at the White House','with the possible exception of when Thomas Jefferson dined alone.');
insert into quotes values (975,'One travels more usefully when alone, because he reflects more.','Thomas Jefferson');
insert into quotes values (976,'Always vote for principle, though you may vote alone, and you may cherish the sweetest reflection that your vote is never lost.','John Quincy Adams');
insert into quotes values (977,'Each player must accept the cards life deals him or her: but once they are in hand, he or she alone must decide how to play the cards in order to win the game.','Voltaire');
insert into quotes values (978,'Justice cannot be for one side alone, but must be for both.','Eleanor Roosevelt');
insert into quotes values (979,'It is better to be alone than in bad company.','George Washington');
insert into quotes values (980,'Perhaps I know best why it is man alone who laughs he alone suffers so deeply that he had to invent laughter.','Friedrich Nietzsche');
insert into quotes values (981,'The soul that sees beauty may sometimes walk alone.','Johann Wolfgang von Goethe');
insert into quotes values (982,'A man is rich in proportion to the number of things he can afford to let alone.','Henry David Thoreau');
insert into quotes values (983,'To Follow by faith alone is to follow blindly.','Benjamin Franklin');
insert into quotes values (984,'You are capable of more than you know. Choose a goal that seems right for you and strive to be the best, however hard the path. Aim high. Behave honorably. Prepare to be alone at times, and to endure failure. Persist! The world needs all you can give.','E. O. Wilson');
insert into quotes values (985,'You can get help from teachers, but you are going to have to learn a lot by yourself, sitting alone in a room.','Dr. Seuss');
insert into quotes values (986,'Unconditional war can no longer lead to unconditional victory. It can no longer serve to settle disputes… can no longer be of concern to great powers alone.','John F. Kennedy');
insert into quotes values (987,'Associate yourself with people of good quality, for it is better to be alone than in bad company.','Booker T. Washington');
insert into quotes values (988,'Virtue is not left to stand alone. He who practices it will have neighbors.','Confucius');
insert into quotes values (989,'An artist is always alone','if he is an artist. No, what the artist needs is loneliness.');
insert into quotes values (990,'The man who goes alone can start today but he who travels with another must wait till that other is ready.','Henry David Thoreau');
insert into quotes values (991,'Being solitary is being alone well: being alone luxuriously immersed in doings of your own choice, aware of the fullness of your won presence rather than of the absence of others. Because solitude is an achievement.','Alice Koller');
insert into quotes values (992,'I have noticed… that men usually leave married women alone and are inclined to treat all wives with respect. This is no great credit to married women.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (993,'I am alone I am always alone no matter what.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (994,'Some of my foster families used to send me to the movies to get me out of the house and there I’d sit all day and way into the night. Up in front, there with the screen so big, a little kid all alone, and I loved it. I loved anything that moved up there and I didn’t miss anything that happened and there was no popcorn either.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (995,'A woman can’t be alone. She needs a man. A man and a woman support and strengthen each other. She just can’t do it by herself.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (996,'I used to think as I looked out on the Hollywood night, ‘There must be thousands of girls sitting alone like me dreaming of being a movie star.’ But I’m not going to worry about them. I’m dreaming the hardest.','Marilyn Monroe');
insert into quotes values (997,'Reason is not automatic. Those who deny it cannot be conquered by it. Do not count on them. Leave them alone.','Ayn Rand');
insert into quotes values (998,'The doer alone learneth.','Friedrich Nietzsche');
insert into quotes values (999,'God writes the Gospel not in the Bible alone, but also on trees, and in the flowers and clouds and stars.','Martin Luther');
insert into quotes values (1000,'There is danger that we lose sight of what our friend is absolutely, while considering what she is to us alone.','Henry David Thoreau');
insert into quotes values (1001,'No face which we can give to a matter will stead us so well at last as the truth. This alone wears well.','Henry David Thoreau');
